<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Defeat Troy to Open College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/12/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-troy-to-open-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/12/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-troy-to-open-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall smiles during the West Virginia baseball game against Troy in the Men's College World Series" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/12/G1_Troy-124.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team opened the Men's College World Series with a 7-5 victory over Troy, Friday afternoon at Charles Schwab Field in Omaha, Nebraska. The Mountaineers improve to 46-15 this season while the Trojans fall to 38-31.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/G1_Troy-124.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/G1_Troy-124.jpg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall smiles during the West Virginia baseball game against Troy in the Men's College World Series</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/G1_Troy-124.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 19:58:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59190</s:story_id></item><item><title>Sabins Named NCBWA Mike Martin National Coach of the Year</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/12/baseball-sabins-named-ncbwa-mike-martin-national-coach-of-the-year</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/12/baseball-sabins-named-ncbwa-mike-martin-national-coach-of-the-year</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Steve Sabins" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/12/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_1547_large.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. (NCBWA) – In the midst of the best season in program history, West Virginia head coach Steve Sabins has been named the 2026 National Collegiate Baseball Writers Association Mike Martin National Coach of the Year.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_1547_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_1547_large.jpg"><media:title>Steve Sabins</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_1547_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 13:46:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59189</s:story_id></item><item><title>Naukot Earns All-America Honors, Kinyanjui Advances to NCAA Final</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/12/track-field-naukot-earns-all-america-honors-kinyanjui-advances-to-ncaa-final</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/12/track-field-naukot-earns-all-america-honors-kinyanjui-advances-to-ncaa-final</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Mercy Kinyanjui competes in the 3,000 meter steeplechase at the NCAA Outdoor Track and Field Championships." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/12/Nationals.KATEADENT-6.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team opened competition at the NCAA Outdoor Championships on Thursday evening at Hayward Field with a pair of standout performances from Joy Naukot and Mercy Kinyanjui.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/Nationals.KATEADENT-6.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/Nationals.KATEADENT-6.jpg"><media:title>Mercy Kinyanjui competes in the 3,000 meter steeplechase at the NCAA Outdoor Track and Field Championships.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/12/Nationals.KATEADENT-6.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:15:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59188</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Set to Open College World Series Against Troy</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-open-college-world-series-against-troy</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-open-college-world-series-against-troy</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Team Huddle at Charles Schwab Field in Omaha" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/11/practice-2.png" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The West Virginia University baseball team will make its College World Series debut on Friday, June 12, as it takes on Troy from Charles Schwab Field in Omaha, Nebraska. First pitch is scheduled for 2 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/practice-2.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/practice-2.png"><media:title>Team Huddle at Charles Schwab Field in Omaha</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/practice-2.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 16:46:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59187</s:story_id></item><item><title>Cutting-Edge Technology Helps Fuel West Virginia’s Run To Omaha</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/baseball-cutting-edge-technology-helps-fuel-west-virginias-run-to-omaha</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/baseball-cutting-edge-technology-helps-fuel-west-virginias-run-to-omaha</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia coach Steve Sabins observes his team practicing at Charles Schwab Field in Omaha, Nebraska, on the eve of West Virginia's first-ever College World Series game against Troy on Friday, June 12, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/11/Sabins-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – I view cutting-edge sports technology probably about the same way some doctors view taking vitamin supplements and fish oil – if you think it's helping you, then by all means, go for it!]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/Sabins-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/Sabins-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia coach Steve Sabins observes his team practicing at Charles Schwab Field in Omaha, Nebraska, on the eve of West Virginia's first-ever College World Series game against Troy on Friday, June 12, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/Sabins-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 16:42:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59186</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Play Troy in First Game of College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-west-virginia-to-play-troy-in-first-game-of-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-west-virginia-to-play-troy-in-first-game-of-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup vs. Troy" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team will play its first game of the Men's College World Series against Troy on Friday, June 12, at 2 p.m. ET. The game will air on ESPN and WVU will be the designated home team.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg"><media:title>Matchup vs. Troy</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 12:21:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59174</s:story_id></item><item><title>Big 12 Conference Announces 2026-27 Men’s Basketball Opponents</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/mens-basketball-big-12-conference-announces-2026-27-mens-basketball-opponents</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/mens-basketball-big-12-conference-announces-2026-27-mens-basketball-opponents</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The Big 12 Conference has announced the 2026-27 scheduling matrix" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/11/MBB26-27_Big12Opponents_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The Big 12 Conference has announced the scheduling matrix for the 2026-27 men's basketball season.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/MBB26-27_Big12Opponents_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/MBB26-27_Big12Opponents_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>The Big 12 Conference has announced the 2026-27 scheduling matrix</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/MBB26-27_Big12Opponents_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59185</s:story_id></item><item><title>Big 12 Releases Women’s Basketball 2026-27 Opponents</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/womens-basketball-big-12-releases-womens-basketball-2026-27-opponents</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/womens-basketball-big-12-releases-womens-basketball-2026-27-opponents</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WBB 2026-27 Big 12 Schedule Matrix" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. - The Big 12 announced the conference scheduling matrix for the 2026-27 women's basketball season. Teams will play three Big 12 opponents twice, then play the other 12 conference opponents one time, for a total of 18 conference games.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png"><media:title>WBB 2026-27 Big 12 Schedule Matrix</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 12:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59183</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Advance to College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the first time in program history, the West Virginia University baseball team is going to the Men's College World Series after finishing off a two-game sweep of Cal Poly in the NCAA Super Regionals with a 17-1 victory over the Mustangs on Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 45-15 on the season, setting a new program record for wins.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg"><media:title>The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 6 Jun 2026 20:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59172</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl, Kelly, Cole Collect All-America Honors</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/10/baseball-yehl-kelly-cole-collect-all-america-honors</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/10/baseball-yehl-kelly-cole-collect-all-america-honors</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chansen Cole, Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – Three members of the West Virginia University baseball team have picked up All-America honors. Redshirt junior Maxx Yehl was named to the first team by Perfect Game and the second team by NCBWA, sophomore Gavin Kelly earned second-team honors by Perfect Game and NCBWA, and sophomore Chansen Cole was named to the second team by NCBWA.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg"><media:title>Chansen Cole, Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 13:37:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59182</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>